\\\\
\blueE{r} &= \dfrac{\maroonD{300}}{\goldE{t}}
\end{align}$

###Rate when trip takes $1.5$ hours?

Let's use our equation to find the value of $\blueE{r}$ when $\goldE{t}=\goldE{1.5}$:

$\begin{align}
\blueE{r} &= \dfrac{\maroonD{300}}{\goldE{t}}
\\\\
&=\dfrac{\maroonD{300}}{\goldE{1.5}}
\\\\
&=\dfrac{600}{3}
\\\\
&=200
\end{align}$

###Writing an equation

