\\\\
\blueE{r} &= \dfrac{\maroonD{48}}{\goldE{t}}
\end{align}$

Let's rewrite this equation so $\goldE{t}$ is by itself:

$\begin{align}
\blueE{r} \cdot \goldE{t} &= \dfrac{\maroonD{48}}{\cancel{\goldE{t}}} \cdot \cancel{\goldE{t}}
\\\\
\blueE{r} \goldE{t} &= \maroonD{48}
\\\\
\dfrac{\cancel{\blueE{r}} \goldE{t}}{\cancel{\blueE{r}}} &= \dfrac{\maroonD{48}}{\blueE{r}}
\\\\
\goldE{t} &= \dfrac{\maroonD{48}}{\blueE{r}}
\end{align}$

